OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FOver-50s who retired at    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fstart of Covid 'much       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fpoorer'                    
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, People over 50 who left work during the
OL,6, pandemic are "much poorer" in general  
OL,7, than other retirees, research suggests.
OL,9,FThe Institute for Fiscal Studies (IFS) 
OL,10,Fsaid 48% of those who retired in       
OL,11,F2020-21 were now living in relative    
OL,12,Fpoverty.                               
OL,14,FThey were less likely to receive a     
OL,15,Fpension and had lower levels of        
OL,16,Fwell-being than other retirees, the IFS
OL,17,Ffound.                                 
OL,19,FIt said disruption from the pandemic   
OL,20,Fand perceived health risks may have    
OL,21,Fforced many to leave work early.       
